                    <img src="/blog/assets/poster/top-10-must-watch-anime-for-beginners.jpg" alt="">
                </div>

                <div class="post-article-box">
                    <p>If you’re new to the world of anime and feeling overwhelmed by the endless choices, don’t worry! We’ve got you covered with a curated list of the top 10 must-watch anime for beginners. Each of these series offers a unique experience and showcases the diversity of anime storytelling. So grab some popcorn, and let’s dive in!</p>

                    <h2><span>1.</span> Naruto</h2>

                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Genre:</span></b> Action, Adventure, Fantasy</p>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Episodes:</span></b> 220 (Naruto) + 500 (Naruto Shippuden)</p>
                    <p>Follow the journey of Naruto Uzumaki, a young ninja with dreams of becoming the Hokage (leader of his village). Packed with emotional moments, epic battles, and themes of friendship and perseverance, Naruto is a perfect starting point for newcomers.</p>

                    <h2><span>2.</span> Attack on Titan</h2>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Genre:</span></b> Action, Mystery, Drama</p>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Episodes:</span></b> 87 (Final season ongoing)</p>
                    <p>This gripping series is set in a world where humanity is on the brink of extinction due to giant humanoid creatures called Titans. With its intense plot twists and breathtaking animation, Attack on Titan will keep you hooked from the very first episode.</p>

                    <h2><span>3.</span> Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba</h2>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Genre:</span></b> Action, Fantasy</p>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Episodes:</span></b> 44 (Season 3 ongoing)</p>
                    <p>Known for its stunning visuals and heartfelt story, Demon Slayer follows Tanjiro Kamado as he embarks on a quest to save his sister and avenge his family. The show’s universal appeal makes it a great choice for beginners. <a href="/search/?s=demon+slayer">- Download Link</a></p>

                    <h2><span>4.</span> Your Name (Kimi no Na wa)</h2>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Genre:</span></b> Romance, Fantasy, Drama</p>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Format:</span></b> Movie</p>
                    <p>If you’re looking for a shorter yet deeply emotional experience, Your Name is a must-watch. This beautifully animated film explores themes of love, fate, and connection as two teenagers mysteriously swap bodies.</p>

                    <h2><span>5.</span> My Hero Academia</h2>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Genre:</span></b> Action, Comedy, Superhero</p>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Episodes:</span></b> 138 (Season 7 announced)</p>
                    <p>In a world where almost everyone has superpowers (called Quirks), Izuku Midoriya dreams of becoming the greatest hero. <a href="/search/?s=My+Hero">My Hero Academia</a> combines action, humor, and heartfelt moments, making it a beginner-friendly series.</p>

                    <h2><span>6.</span> One Punch Man</h2>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Genre:</span></b> Action, Comedy, Superhero</p>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Episodes:</span></b> 24 (2 seasons)</p>
                    <p>This hilarious take on the superhero genre follows Saitama, a hero who can defeat any opponent with a single punch. Its over-the-top action and comedic moments make it a great pick for newcomers. <a href="/search/?s=one+punch">- Download Link</a></p>

                    <h2><span>7.</span> Death Note</h2>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Genre:</span></b> Mystery, Supernatural, Thriller</p>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Episodes:</span></b> 37</p>
                    <p>A psychological thriller that keeps you on the edge of your seat, <a href="/search/?s=death+note">Death Note</a> follows Light Yagami, a student who gains the power to kill anyone by writing their name in a mysterious notebook. It’s a must-watch for fans of mind games and moral dilemmas.</p>

                    <h2><span>8.</span> Spirited Away</h2>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Genre:</span></b> Fantasy, Adventure</p>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Format:</span></b> Movie</p>
                    <p>Studio Ghibli’s masterpiece Spirited Away takes you on a magical journey as Chihiro, a young girl, navigates a mysterious spirit world. This enchanting film is perfect for viewers of all ages.</p>

                    <h2><span>9.</span> Hunter x Hunter (2011)</h2>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Genre:</span></b> Adventure, Fantasy</p>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Episodes:</span></b> 148</p>
                    <p>Gon Freecss embarks on an adventure to become a Hunter and find his father. With its rich world-building and compelling characters, Hunter x Hunter is an excellent introduction to long-running anime series.</p>

                    <h2><span>10.</span> Haikyuu!!</h2>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Genre:</span></b> Sports, Comedy, Drama</p>
                    <p class="no-mb"><b><span>Episodes:</span></b> 85 (Final movie announced)</p>
                    <p>Even if you’re not into sports, Haikyuu!! will win you over with its exhilarating volleyball matches and inspiring characters. It’s a feel-good series that’s easy to fall in love with.</p>

                    <h2><span>10.</span> Final Thoughts</h2>
                    <p>Whether you’re into action-packed adventures, heartfelt dramas, or magical fantasies, these anime are sure to ignite your love for the medium. Each series on this list offers something special and serves as a fantastic gateway into the diverse world of anime.</p>
                    <p><b>So, which one are you starting with?</b></p>
                </div>
